data-message-id=3D"5415ce83-7b6f-411e-9fd7-67cec3389df2" dir=3D"auto" class= =3D"min-h-8 text-message flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 whitespace-no= rmal break-words [.text-message+&]:mt-5"><div class=3D"flex w-full flex= -col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[3px]"><div class=3D"markdown prose w-full= break-words dark:prose-invert dark"><p>To determine the average <strong>bo= uncing range</strong> in trading, you would want to use indicators that hel= p identify <strong>support and resistance levels</strong> as well as volati= lity. Here are some key strategies and indicators that can help you achieve= this:</p><h3>1. <strong>Bollinger Bands</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>How i= t works</strong>: Bollinger Bands consist of three lines: a middle simple m= oving average (SMA), and two outer bands that represent volatility based on= standard deviations from the SMA.</li><li><strong>Why it's useful</strong>= : The price often "bounces" between the upper and lower bands, making it ea= sier to visualize the range. If the price touches the lower band, it often = signals a bounce back up toward the middle or upper band.</li></ul><h3>2. <= strong>ATR (Average True Range)</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>How it works</= strong>: ATR measures market volatility by averaging the true range over a = specific period.</li><li><strong>Why it's useful</strong>: It helps estimat= e the size of price movements, giving an idea of how much the price could m= ove (or "bounce") within a set period.</li></ul><h3>3. <strong>Pivot Points= </strong></h3><ul><li><strong>How it works</strong>: Pivot points are calcu= lated based on the high, low, and close prices of the previous trading day = to identify potential support and resistance levels.</li><li><strong>Why it= 's useful</strong>: These levels act as boundaries for the average range wi= thin which the price may bounce.</li></ul><h3>4. <strong>RSI (Relative Stre= ngth Index)</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>How it works</strong>: RSI measure= s the momentum of price movements. It is typically used to identify overbou= ght and oversold conditions, which can indicate possible bounce points.</li= ><li><strong>Why it's useful</strong>: When RSI approaches extreme levels (= over 70 or below 30), it can signal that a price reversal is likely, indica= ting the range=E2=80=99s turning points.</li></ul><h3>5. <strong>Fibonacci = Retracement Levels</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>How it works</strong>: Fibo= nacci levels are drawn based on a prior high and low, with key levels such = as 38.2%, 50%, and 61.8%.</li><li><strong>Why it's useful</strong>: These l= evels often act as support and resistance, helping you identify potential a= reas where price might bounce within a range.</li></ul><h3>6. <strong>Donch= ian Channels</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>How it works</strong>: Donchian C= hannels plot the highest high and the lowest low over a specific period, fo= rming a range.</li><li><strong>Why it's useful</strong>: It gives clear bou= ndaries within which the price can bounce, similar to Bollinger Bands, but = focusing more on recent highs and lows.</li></ul><h3>Combining Indicators</= h3><p>To better capture the <strong>bouncing range</strong>, you might comb= ine Bollinger Bands (for volatility), ATR (to understand potential movement= size), and support/resistance levels using Pivot Points or Fibonacci retra= cements. This multi-faceted approach can give you a well-rounded view of th= e price range and potential bounce areas.</p><p>Let me know if you'd like m= ore details on any specific indicator or strategy!</p></div></div></div></d= iv></div></div></div></div></article><article class=3D"w-full text-token-te= xt-primary focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-[-4px]" dir= =3D"auto" rsion=3D5 strategy("MACD & RSI Strategy", overlay=3Dtrue) // MACD settings fast_length =3D 12 slow_length =3D 26 signal_smoothing =3D 9 [macdLine, signalLine, _] =3D ta.macd(close, fast_length, 30).</li><li>A sell is triggered only when the RSI is <str= ong>above</strong> the overbought threshold (e.g., 70).</li></ul></li></ol>= <h3>Modifications:</h3><ul><li>You can adjust the thresholds = XAU/USD:</p><ul><li><strong>RSI Overbought Level</strong>: We can raise thi= s to <strong>80</strong> (from 70) since XAU/USD tends to have longer bulli= sh trends, and reaching 70 may trigger overlay=3Dtrue) // MACD settings fast_length =3D 12 slow_length =3D 26 signal_smoothing =3D 9 [macdLine, signalLine, _] =3D ta.macd(close, fast_length, slow_length, sign= al_smoothing) // Adjusted RSI XAU/USD or your timeframe).</= li><li><code>trail_stop</code> is updated as the price moves higher to ensu= re that it only tightens as the price rises, protecting profits.</li></ul><= /li><li><p><strong>Buy and Sell Conditions</strong>:</p><ul><li>The MACD cr= ossover and RSI criteria remain the same.</li><li>When the buy condition is= met, the strategy enters a long iling stop-loss is enforced, meaning it will close the trade if the price d= rops by more than the <code>trail_offset</code> from the highest point sinc= e entry.</li></ul></li></ol><p>This script XAU/USD rsiLength =3D 14 rsiOverbought =3D 80 // Higher threshold for a trending market rsiOversold =3D 40 // Less aggressive threshold for catching dips rsi =3D ta.rsi(close, rsiLength) // Buy condition: MACD crossover + RSI is below adjusted oversold level (40= ) buyCondition =3D ta.crossover(macdLine, signalLine) and rsi < rsiOversol= d // Sell condition: MACD crossunder + RSI is above hljs language-pinescript">//@version=3D5 strategy("MACD & RSI with Trailing Stop for Long and Short (Fixed Exits= )", overlay=3Dtrue) // MACD settings fast_length =3D 12 slow_length =3D 26 signal_smoothing =3D 9 [macdLine, signalLine, _] =3D ta.macd(close, fast_length, slow_length, sign= al_smoothing) // Adjusted RSI settings for XAU/USD rsiLength =3D 14 rsiOverbought =3D 75 // Adjusted to fit the trending nature of gold rsiOversold =3D 45 // Higher oversold level for more buy signals rsi =3D ta.rsi(close, rsiLength) // Buy condition: MACD crossover + RSI below oversold level (45) buyCondition =3D ta.crossover(macdLine, signalLine) and rsi < rsiOversol= d // Sell condition: MACD crossunder + RSI above overbought level (75) sellCondition =3D ta.crossunder(macdLine, signalLine) and rsi > rsiOverb= ought // Trailing stop-loss settings with offset of 50 trail_offset_long =3D 50 // Trail by $50 for long positions trail_offset_short =3D 50 // Trail by $50 for short positions // Define variables to hold the trailing stop levels and initialize with a = proper type var float trail_stop_long =3D na var float trail_stop_short =3D na // Long position trailing stop logic if (strategy.position_size > 0) // If in a long position trail_stop_long :=3D math.max(trail_stop_long, close - trail_offset_lon= g) // Update trailing stop as the price moves up strategy.exit("Trailing Stop Long", stop=3Dtrail_stop_long) // Short position trailing stop logic if (strategy.position_size < 0) // If in a short position trail_stop_short :=3D math.min(trail_stop_short, close + trail_offset_s= hort) // Update trailing stop as the price moves down strategy.exit("Trailing Stop Short", stop=3Dtrail_stop_short) // Close the long position if the sell condition is met if (strategy.position_size > 0 and sellCondition) strategy.close("Buy", comment=3D"MACD Sell Condition") // Close the short position if the buy condition is met if (strategy.position_size < 0 and buyCondition) strategy.close("Sell", comment=3D"MACD Buy Condition") // Execute buy and sell orders if (buyCondition) strategy.entry("Buy", strategy.long) if (sellCondition) strategy.entry("Sell", strategy.short) // Plot MACD and RSI for visualization plot(macdLine, color=3Dcolor.blue, title=3D"MACD Line") plot(signalLine, color=3Dcolor.red, title=3D"Signal Line") hline(75, "RSI Overbought", color=3Dcolor.red) hline(45, "RSI Oversold", color=3Dcolor.green) </code></div></div></pre><h3>Key Fixes:</h3><ol><li><p><strong>Ensure Prope= r Trade Exits</strong>:</p><ul><li>The script explicitly fill=3D"currentColor"></path></svg>Kopier kode</button></s= pan></div></div></div><div class=3D"overflow-y-auto p-4" dir=3D"ltr"><code = class=3D"!whitespace-pre hljs language-pinescript">//@version=3D5 strategy("MACD & RSI with Take-Profit and Partial Close", overlay=3Dtru= e, default_qty_type=3Dstrategy.percent_of_equity, default_qty_value=3D50) // Set the initial capital to $500 strategy.risk.allow_entry_in(strategy.direction.long) strategy.risk.allow_entry_in(strategy.direction.short) strategy.initial_capital(500) // MACD settings fast_length =3D 12 slow_length =3D 26 signal_smoothing =3D 9 [macdLine, signalLine, _] =3D ta.macd(close, fast_length, slow_length, sign= al_smoothing) // Adjusted RSI settings for XAU/USD rsiLength =3D 14 rsiOverbought =3D 75 // Higher threshold for trending markets rsiOversold =3D 45 // Higher oversold level for frequent buy signals rsi =3D ta.rsi(close, rsiLength) // Buy condition: MACD crossover + RSI below oversold level (45) buyCondition =3D ta.crossover(macdLine, signalLine) and rsi < rsiOversol= d // Sell condition: MACD crossunder + RSI above overbought level (75) sellCondition =3D ta.crossunder(macdLine, signalLine) and rsi > rsiOverb= ought // Take-profit level (30% increase) takeProfitPercentage =3D 1.30 // Calculate long and short take-profit prices longTakeProfitPrice =3D strategy.position_avg_price * takeProfitPercentage shortTakeProfitPrice =3D strategy.position_avg_price / takeProfitPercentage // Execute buy orders if (buyCondition) strategy.entry("Buy", strategy.long) // Execute sell orders if (sellCondition) strategy.entry("Sell", strategy.short) // Take-profit for long position (sell 30% of the position when 30% profit = is reached) if (strategy.position_size > 0) strategy.exit("Take Profit Long", from_entry=3D"Buy", limit=3DlongTakeP= rofitPrice, qty_percent=3D30) // Take-profit for short position (cover 30% of the position when 30% profi= t is reached) if (strategy.position_size < 0) strategy.exit("Take Profit Short", from_entry=3D"Sell", limit=3DshortTa= keProfitPrice, qty_percent=3D30) // Close long position when sell condition is met if (strategy.position_size > 0 and sellCondition) strategy.close("Buy", comment=3D"MACD Sell Condition") // Close short position when buy condition is met if (strategy.position_size < 0 and buyCondition) strategy.close("Sell", comment=3D"MACD Buy Condition") // Plot MACD and RSI for visualization plot(macdLine, color=3Dcolor.blue, title=3D"MACD Line") plot(signalLine, color=3Dcolor.red, title=3D"Signal Line") hline(75, "RSI Overbought", color=3Dcolor.red) hline(45, "RSI Oversold", color=3Dcolor.green) </code></div></div></pre><h3>Key Changes:</h3><ol><li><p><strong>Take-Profi= t Mechanism</strong>:</p><ul><li>We calculate the <strong>take-profit level= </strong> as a 30% increase for long positions and a 30% decrease for short= positions.</li><li>The <code>strategy.exit()</code> function is used to cl= ose <strong>30% of the position</strong> when the take-profit level is reac= hed.</li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Partial Close (30%)</strong>:</p><ul><li>= <code>qty_percent=3D30</code> in <code>strategy.exit()</code> specifies tha= t <strong>only 30% of the position</strong> is closed when the take-profit = price is hit.</li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Long and Short Position Handling= </strong>:</p><ul><li>The take-profit for long positions triggers when the = price increases by 30%, and for short positions, it triggers when the price= decreases by 30%.</li></ul></li></ol><p>With this setup, the script will p= artially close 30% of the position when a 30% profit is achieved, while sti= ll allowing the remaining position to stay open until the final exit condit= ion is met. language-pinescript">//@version=3D5 strategy("MACD & RSI with 4% Take-Profit and Leverage Simulation", over= lay=3Dtrue, default_qty_type=3Dstrategy.percent_of_equity, default_qty_valu= e=3D50) // (75) sellCondition =3D ta.crossunder(macdLine, signalLine) and rsi > rsiOverb= ought // Take-profit level (4% increase) takeProfitPercentage =3D 1.04 // Calculate long and short take-profit prices <strong>"Short"</strong>. This helps ensure tha= t the correct trade is referenced for both the take-profit and exit conditi= ons.</li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Take-Profit Linked to Entry</strong>:</p>= <ul><li>The <code>strategy.exit()</code> now references the specific entry = (<code>from_entry=3D"Long"</code> or <code>from_entry=3D"Short"</code>) to = ensure the take-profit logic is applied to the correct position.</li></ul><= /li><li><p><strong>Fallback Exit Condition</strong>:</p><ul><li>A <strong>f= allback exit condition</strong> has been added to ensure that, even if the = take-profit isn=E2=80=99t reached, the position will still close when the o= pposite condition (e.g., a sell signal for long trades) is met.</li></ul></= li></ol><h3>Notes:</h3><ul><li>If you are simulating <strong>100x leverage<= /strong>, make sure to set it in the <strong>strategy settings</strong> wit= hin TradingView. The leverage cannot be directly coded in Pine Script.</li>= <li>Test this update by running it through a backtest, and it should now tr= igger both take-profit and exit trades language-pinescript">//= @version=3D5 strategy("MACD & RSI with 4% Take-Profit and Higher Contracts", overlay= =3Dtrue, default_qty_type=3Dstrategy.percent_of_equity, default_qty_value= =3D80) // MACD settings fast_length =3D 12 slow_length =3D 26 signal_smoothing =3D 9 [macdLine, signalLine, _] =3D ta.macd(close, fast_length, slow_length, sign= al_smoothing) // Adjusted RSI settings for XAU/USD rsiLength =3D 14 rsiOverbought =3D 75 // Higher threshold for trending markets rsiOversold =3D 45 // Higher oversold level for frequent buy signals rsi =3D ta.rsi(close, rsiLength) // Buy condition: MACD crossover + RSI below oversold level (45) buyCondition =3D ta.crossover(macdLine, signalLine) and rsi < rsiOversol= d // Sell condition: MACD crossunder + RSI above overbought level (75) sellCondition =3D ta.crossunder(macdLine, signalLine) and rsi > rsiOverb= ought // Take-profit level (4% increase) takeProfitPercentage =3D 1.04 // Calculate long and short take-profit prices longTakeProfitPrice =3D strategy.position_avg_price * takeProfitPercentage shortTakeProfitPrice =3D strategy.position_avg_price / takeProfitPercentage // Execute buy orders with an explicit name "Long" if (buyCondition) strategy.entry("Long", strategy.long) // Execute sell orders with an explicit name "Short" if (sellCondition) strategy.entry("Short", strategy.short) // Take-profit for long position (sell 30% of the position when 4% profit i= s reached) if (strategy.position_size > 0) strategy.exit("Take Profit Long", from_entry=3D"Long", limit=3DlongTake= ProfitPrice, qty_percent=3D30) // Take-profit for short position (cover 30% of the position when 4% profit= is reached) if (strategy.position_size < 0) strategy.exit("Take Profit Short", from_entry=3D"Short", limit=3DshortT= akeProfitPrice, qty_percent=3D30) // Fallback close logic in case take-profit doesn't trigger if (strategy.position_size > 0 and sellCondition) strategy.close("Long", comment=3D"Fallback MACD Sell Condition") if (strategy.position_size < 0 and buyCondition) strategy.close("Short", comment=3D"Fallback MACD Buy Condition") // Enable pyramiding for multiple positions strategy.risk.allow_entry_in(strategy.direction.long, 10) // Allow up to 1= 0 long entries strategy.risk.allow_entry_in(strategy.direction.short, 10) // Allow up to = 10 short entries // Plot MACD and RSI for visualization plot(macdLine, color=3Dcolor.blue, title=3D"MACD Line") plot(signalLine, color=3Dcolor.red, title=3D"Signal Line") hline(75, "RSI Overbought", color=3Dcolor.red) hline(45, "RSI Oversold", color=3Dcolor.green) </code></div></div></pre><h3>Key Adjustments:</h3><ol><li><p><strong>Increa= sed Position Size</strong>:</p><ul><li>The position size is now set to <str= ong>80%</strong> of equity, which increases the number of contracts per tra= de.</li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Allow Pyramiding</strong>:</p><ul><li>The = script allows up to <strong>10 simultaneous long and short positions</stron= g> using the <code>strategy.risk.allow_entry_in()</code> function. This ena= bles you to take on more trades even when positions are already open.</li><= /ul></li><li><p><strong>Take-Profit and Exit Logic</strong> remain the same= to ensure profitable trades are closed when the conditions are met.</p></l= i></ol><p>By increasing the position size to 80% of equity and allowing mul= tiple entries (pyramiding), this should increase the number of contracts tr= aded in the backtest. empty:hidden first:pt-[3px]= "><div class=3D"markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert dark"><= p>Let's troubleshoot the issues you're facing:</p><h3>Potential Problems:</= h3><ol><li><strong>Pyramiding and Position Size</strong>: When using pyrami= ding with large position sizes (like 80% of equity), there could be problem= s with <strong>exceeding available margin</strong>, especially if you're si= mulating 100x leverage. This could cause trades to fail or not open as expe= cted.</li><li><strong>Overlapping Conditions</strong>: If the script opens = multiple entries (due to pyramiding) but doesn't manage exits properly, it = might cause conflicting positions or unexpected behavior in the backtest.</= li><li><strong>Leverage and Risk Management</strong>: If leverage isn't pro= perly set in the strategy settings or if the risk management logic isn=E2= =80=99t working correctly, it might fail to manage the position size, resul= ting in unintended behavior.</li></ol><h3>Steps to Fix:</h3><ol><li><strong= >Adjust Pyramiding and Risk Settings</strong>: Reduce the maximum number of= pyramiding entries to prevent over-leveraging.</li><li><strong>Ensure Corr= ect Leverage in TradingView Settings</strong>: Since Pine Script can=E2=80= =99t control leverage directly, ensure you=E2=80=99ve properly set 100x lev= erage in the TradingView properties.</li><li><strong>Improve Exit Logic</st= rong>: Ensure that each entry is tied to an appropriate exit, especially wh= en using pyramiding. This avoids open trades not being closed correctly.</l= i></ol><p>Here=E2=80=99s the modified script with more careful handling of = <strong>pyramiding and exits</strong>:</p><h3>Modified Take-Profit and Improved Exits", overlay= =3Dtrue, default_qty_type=3Dstrategy.percent_of_equity, default_qty_value= =3D50) // MACD settings fast_length =3D 12 slow_length =3D 26 signal_smoothing =3D 9 [macdLine, signalLine, _] =3D ta.macd(close, fast_length, slow_length, sign= al_smoothing) // Adjusted RSI settings for XAU/USD rsiLength =3D 14 rsiOverbought =3D 75 // Higher threshold for trending markets rsiOversold =3D 45 // Higher oversold level for frequent buy signals rsi =3D ta.rsi(close, rsiLength) // Buy condition: MACD crossover + RSI below oversold level (45) buyCondition =3D 4% profit= is reached) if (strategy.position_size < 0) strategy.exit("Take Profit Short", from_entry=3D"Short", limit=3DshortT= akeProfitPrice, qty_percent=3D30) // Fallback close logic in case take-profit doesn't trigger if (strategy.position_size > 0 and sellCondition) strategy.close("Long", comment=3D"Fallback MACD Sell Condition") if (strategy.position_size < 0 and buyCondition) strategy.close("Short", comment=3D"Fallback MACD Buy Condition") // Enable controlled pyramiding (limit to 3 positions to avoid over-leverag= ing) strategy.risk.max_position_size(3) // Plot MACD and Oversold", color=3Dcolor.green) </code></div></div></pre><h3>Changes Made:</h3><ol><li><strong>Position Siz= e Control</strong>: We now check that no long or short position is already = open before placing another one. You can increase this based = on your risk tolerance, but it=E2=80=99s safer to start with a lower limit.= </li><li><strong>Fallback Close</strong>: Ensured that the fallback close c= onditions always attempt to exit the position when the opposite signal occu= rs, which should prevent positions from being left open.</li><li><strong>Po= sition Size</strong>: Still uses 50% of equity, but with leverage, you will= be trading much larger contracts.</li></ol><h3>Setting Leverage:</h3><ul><= li>Ensure you have <strong>100x leverage</strong> enabled in the TradingVie= w strategy settings by:<ol><li>Right-clicking the chart.</li><li>Going to <= strong>Settings > Properties</strong>.</li><li>Setting <strong>Leverage<= /strong> to 100x.</li></ol></li></ul><p>This should give you more controlle= d pyramiding and better trade exits. takeProfitPercentage =3D 1.04 // Calculate long and short take-profit prices longTakeProfitPrice =3D strategy.position_avg_price * takeProfitPercentage shortTakeProfitPrice =3D strategy.position_avg_price / takeProfitPercentage // Execute buy orders with an explicit name "Long" // Ensure we are not already in a long position by using 'strategy.opentrad= es =3D=3D 0' if (buyCondition and strategy.opentrades =3D=3D 0) strategy.entry("Long", strategy.long) // Execute sell orders with an explicit name "Short" // Ensure we are not already in a short position by using i= s reached) if (strategy.position_size > 0) strategy.exit("Take Profit Long", from_entry=3D"Long", limit=3DlongTake= ProfitPrice, qty_percent=3D30) // Take-profit for short position (cover 30% of logic in case take-profit doesn't trigger if (strategy.position_size > 0 and sellCondition) strategy.close("Long", comment=3D"Fallback MACD Sell Condition") if (strategy.position_size < 0 and buyCondition) strategy.close("Short", comment=3D"Fallback MACD Buy Condition") // Control pyramiding: allow up to 3 positions strategy.risk.max_position_size(3) // Plot MACD and RSI for visualization is met if (strategy.position_size < 0 and buyCondition) strategy.close("Short", comment=3D"Fallback MACD Buy Condition") // Control pyramiding: allow up to 3 positions (can be adjusted as needed) strategy.risk.max_position_size(3) // Plot MACD and RSI for visualization plot(macdLine, color=3Dcolor.blue, title=3D"MACD Line") plot(signalLine, color=3Dcolor.red, title=3D"Signal Line") hline(75, 100 // Calculate TP points based on position type float tp1 =3D na, tp2 =3D na, tp3 =3D na, tp4 =3D na, tp5 =3D na if (positionType =3D=3D "Long" and buyPrice > 0) tp1 :=3D buyPrice * (1 + tp_interval) tp2 :=3D buyPrice * (1 + tp_interval * 2) tp3 :=3D buyPrice * (1 + tp_interval * 3) tp4 :=3D buyPrice * (1 + tp_interval * 4) tp5 :=3D buyPrice * (1 + tp_interval * 5) =20 if tp_interval * 4) tp5 :=3D buyPrice * (1 - tp_interval * 5) // Plot TP levels on the chart plot(tp1, title=3D"TP1", color=3Dcolor.green, linewidth=3D2, style=3Dplot.s= tyle_line, offset=3D0, plot(tp5, title=3D"TP5", color=3Dcolor.green, linewidth=3D2, style=3Dplot.s= tyle_line, offset=3D0, display=3Ddisplay.all) // Label the TP levels on the chart if (not na(tp1)) label.new(x=3Dbar_index, rmat.mintick), style=3Dlabel.style_label_up, color=3Dcolor.green, textcolor= =3Dcolor.white) </code></div></div></pre><h3>How It Works:</h3><ol><li><p><strong>User Inpu= t</strong>:</p><ul><li>Enter
